Q: &ldquo;How is data immutability in private channels implemented in Fabric? How can one establish which ledger stores valid history of transactions, if one party has forged data on its peer???&rdquo;
Before beginning here is some fabric terminology I’ll be using in the post (all referenced from Here.)
Channel - A Hyperledger Fabric channel is a private “subnet” of communication between two or more specific network members, for conducting private and confidential transactions.
